#. <section class="sutta" id="sn48.169-178"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn48.169-178:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 48"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 48"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn48.169-178:0.2"
msgid "15. Punaoghavagga"
msgstr "15. Another Chapter on Floods"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn48.169-178:0.3"
msgid "169–​178. punaoghādisutta"
msgstr "169–​178. Another Series on Floods, Etc."

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.243"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn48.169-178:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, uddhambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni."
msgstr ""
"(To be expanded as in SN 45.171–179, with the following as the final "
"discourse, removal of greed version.) “Mendicants, there are five higher "
"fetters."

msgctxt "sn48.169-178:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "sn48.169-178:1.3"
msgid "Rūparāgo, arūparāgo, māno, uddhaccaṃ, avijjā—"
msgstr ""
"Desire for rebirth in the realm of luminous form, desire for rebirth in the "
"formless realm, conceit, restlessness, and ignorance."

msgctxt "sn48.169-178:1.4"
msgid "imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañcuddhambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni."
msgstr "These are the five higher fetters."

msgctxt "sn48.169-178:1.5"
msgid ""
"Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ uddhambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ abhiññāya "
"pariññāya parikkhayāya pahānāya pañcindriyāni bhāvetabbāni."
msgstr ""
"The five faculties should be developed for the direct knowledge, complete "
"understanding, finishing, and giving up of these five higher fetters."

msgctxt "sn48.169-178:1.6"
msgid "Katamāni pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "sn48.169-178:1.7"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu saddhindriyaṃ bhāveti rāgavinayapariyosānaṃ "
"dosavinayapariyosānaṃ mohavinayapariyosānaṃ. Vīriyindriyaṃ … pe … "
"satindriyaṃ … samādhindriyaṃ … paññindriyaṃ bhāveti rāgavinayapariyosānaṃ "
"dosavinayapariyosānaṃ mohavinayapariyosānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant develops the faculties of faith, energy, mindfulness, "
"immersion, and wisdom, which culminate in the removal of greed, hate, and "
"delusion."

msgctxt "sn48.169-178:1.8"
msgid ""
"Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ uddhambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ abhiññāya "
"pariññāya parikkhayāya pahānāya imāni pañcindriyāni bhāvetabbānī”ti."
msgstr ""
"These five faculties should be developed for the direct knowledge, complete "
"understanding, finishing, and giving up of these five higher fetters.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn48.169-178:1.9"
msgid "Oghavaggo sattarasamo."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn48.169-178:2.1"
msgid "Ogho yogo upādānaṃ,"
msgstr "Floods, bonds, grasping,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn48.169-178:2.2"
msgid "ganthā anusayena ca;"
msgstr "ties, and underlying tendencies,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn48.169-178:2.3"
msgid "Kāmaguṇā nīvaraṇā,"
msgstr "kinds of sensual stimulation, hindrances,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn48.169-178:2.4"
msgid "khandhā oruddhambhāgiyāti."
msgstr "aggregates, and fetters high and low."

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "sn48.169-178:2.5"
msgid "Indriyasaṃyuttaṃ catutthaṃ."
msgstr "The Linked Discourses on the Faculties is the fourth section."
